    <prj:ScienceGoal mode="Other">
        <prj:name>Polarization in OH 231.8+4.2</prj:name>
        <prj:note>We propose to study the role of magnetic fields in the shaping of Post-AGB stars and particularly how these can launch and collimate the outlows in those objects, via dust continuum polarization analysis at ~345 GHz. OH231.8+4.2 displays an asymmetrical bipolar morphology and is characterized by a strong bipolar outflow. We therefore propose to detect the field at small scales (close to the central star) and test the launching mechanism, as well as compare the distribution of the magnetic field from our polarization study with the results derived from previous investigations (e.g. maser studies) for multiscale analysis.

The proposed setup will therefore allow us to balance the angular resolution needed to resolve small scale structures and the sensitivity needed to reach 0.1% calibration accuracy in polarized emission intensity, as well as unveil any faint extended emission.</prj:note>
